    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just do <code>String str = System.out.printf(\"%.2f\", val).replace(\",\", \".\");</code> if you want to ensure that independently of the Locale of the user, you will always get / display a \".\" as decimal separator. This is a must if you don't want to make your program crash if you later do some kind of conversion like <code>float f = Float.parseFloat(str);</code></p>\n"
